National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with senior Chinese officials in Beijing to prepare for President Obama's visit to China in September. They discussed bilateral, regional, and global issues of mutual interest, including strengthening the global humanitarian system, sustainable development, and climate change. They also discussed the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and managing differences constructively. Ambassador Rice also met with military and political officials to discuss military-military relations, cyber commitments, human rights, and security issues. In her meeting with President Xi Jinping, they noted the progress in bilateral relations and affirmed the commitment to deepen the bilateral relationship.